name: Mask
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:A white mask modeled after a fox. It's not expensive, but it's well-
maintained and slightly warm to the touch. The feelings of the person
who gave it might indeed reside in this imitation.>

description:
A candle that seems to have withstood the test of
time. Its short wick is blackened, and the white
wax has faded, but if lit, it would likely
remember its purpose.
name: Candle
note: HideItemNumber

description:
A matchstick painted red. Once holding many fires,
this phosphorous sibling might offer some help in
dispelling darkness when struck.
name: Match
note: HideItemNumber

description:
A worn-out wooden bucket. The robustness has been
lost from the bucket that has held water many
times, and it remains forgotten, no longer serving
its purpose of quenching thirst.
name: Bucket
note: HideItemNumber

name: Small Plate
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:A small earthenware dish smaller than the palm of a hand. It was a
pair of couple dishes with a faint chip on the edge, but one half has
been lost for a long time, making a lonely sound.>

description:
Hand-knitted rope. Although it is old, the
skillfully twisted fibers are durable and capable
of realizing the wish to withstand weight and the
hope of tying knots.
name: Rope
note: HideItemNumber

description:
A bucket attached to a rope, a tsurube. The two
tools tied together might remember the old days
when they were immersed in well water.
name: Well Bucket
note:
HideItemNumber

name: Dish filled with water
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:A terracotta plate filled with water. The edge is already chipped, but
the clear water may provide some moisture and a trigger to recall the
past.>

name: Rusted Key
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:A key covered in red rust. It seems like it would easily break with
just one use, but there may come a time when one must proceed, even if
it means sacrificing it.>

name: Hoe
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:An old farming tool. The hoe, worn thin from being gripped, was once
used to obtain sustenance. However, its owner fell ill and it has not
been used for a long time.>

description:
A beautiful tortoiseshell hair ornament. It was
meant to be a gift for someone, but it has faded a
bit because it has never been used and has been
sleeping.
name: Beautiful Hairpin
note: HideItemNumber

description:
Iron scissors. A blade made from old iron, the
sharpness is dull, but it is well known since
ancient times that scissors have more than one
use.
name: Sturdy Scissors
note: HideItemNumber

description:
Incense in an old, musty sachet. The small amount
of fragrant wood left in the tattered bag faintly
retains a nostalgic scent.
name: Ancient Incense
note: HideItemNumber

name: Ancient Letter
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:A letter that has been exposed to the wind and rain for a long time,
with almost all of its characters faded away. You can feel the clumsy
emotions embedded in the short sentences.>

description:
An old amulet bag. It contains a talisman wishing
for safety and someone's name, but it is stained
with blood, indicating that it failed to protect
its owner.
name: Safety Prayer Charm
note: HideItemNumber

name: Old Flashlight (Without Batteries)
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:A mysterious flashlight imbued with a strange power. It's unusable
because the batteries are empty. The handle is inscribed with the
mantra of the Great Sun Buddha; one wonders what the owner wanted to
illuminate.>

description:
A dry cell battery left behind by a ghost who left
their feelings behind. For some reason, it's not
dirty and feels as if it was left behind for
someone.
name: Beautiful Battery
note: HideItemNumber

description:
An old flashlight. The handle is inscribed with
the mantra of Dainichi Nyorai, and it can
illuminate things that are invisible to the eye.
However, light is easily seen from the darkness.
name: Old Pocket Flashlight
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:An old flashlight. The mantra of Mahavairocana is written on the
handle, and it can illuminate things that are invisible to the eye.
However, light is easily seen from the darkness.>

description:
Covered in rust. It would probably break after one
use.
name: Rusted Large Key
note: HideItemNumber

name: Soul-Collecting Talisman
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:A special talisman created by a psychic who has undergone long and
arduous training. It converts people's thoughts into power to exorcise
demons and grudges. Although it has lost its power, it can exert its
effect again by gathering good intentions. Will the talisman be able
to dispel the regrets of its creator?>

name: Remnant Flames of Admiration
note:
<ExtendDesc:The purified spirit's feelings of gratitude have turned into a flame.
In the cursed house, positive thoughts remain as fire, seeking a place
to reside. By gathering them on the talisman, it might be possible to
burn away the curse of restraint.>

description:
A doll's torso clad in a kimono of Japanese style.
It is faintly warm and smaller than usual. It
seems to be modeled after a girl, but...
name: Doll's Torso
note: HideItemNumber

name: Rusted Kodachi
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:An old short sword stuck in a large tree. It is filled with the strong
prayers of people. Although it is deeply rusted, the power to pierce
through the hardened curse remains.>

name: Rusted Iron Key
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:An iron key that was inside the bag. It is terribly old, but there is
no problem using it. Slightly curved as if to indicate the fate of its
owner, it is covered with reddish-brown rust.>

name: Crossing the Suspension Bridge
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:A picture book with a large suspension bridge. On the other side of
the suspension bridge, a goat is waving its hand, and it seems to be
about the protagonist sheep gathering courage to meet a friend.>

name: Singing Princess
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:A picture book about a princess who sings in a castle. It seems to be
about a princess who is always singing, gets banished from the castle,
and becomes friends with the forest animals through her singing.>

name: King's Tail
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:A picture book depicting a king with his back turned. It seems to be
about a king with a tail who sets out on a journey with his soldiers
to remove the tail, but realizes that it is more important to be
accepted for having the tail than to lose it.>

name: Prince of Chocolate
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:A picture book depicting a prince stirring a pot. It seems to be about
a gluttonous prince who hoarded chocolate for himself, but then
realizes that eating together with everyone is more delicious than
eating alone.>

name: Blue Mermaid Princess
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:A picture book about a mermaid girl. The story seems to be about a
mermaid daughter who is entrusted to humans, grows up beautifully, but
her foster parents are deceived by a villain and she is sold to a
human trafficker.>

name: Match and Girl
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:A picture book about a girl who lit a fire. In the cold town, it seems
to be about a girl trying to sell matches, who sees the figure of her
deceased grandmother in the small flame.>

name: Bat's Friend
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:A picture book with a crying bat. In a forest where beasts and birds
quarrel, the bat claimed to be friends with both, but in the end, it
seems to be disliked by both sides.>

name: Happy Prince
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:A picture book with an image of a prince's statue and a swallow. It
seems to be about a swallow that tries hard to fulfill the wish of the
immobile prince's statue, but in doing so, it ends up losing something
important.>

name: Little Rabbit
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:A small rabbit that came out of a hole in the library. It's fluffy and
warm, but it doesn't seem to be a living creature. The talkative
rabbit seems to have been looking for someone who loves books for a
long time.>

name: Doll's Right Arm
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:The right arm of the doll. The hand that harbors a faint warmth has
its fingers firmly spread open. The extended little fingers might be
hoping for a future where they can hold someone's hand.>

name: Doll's Left Arm
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:The doll's left arm. The faintly warm small hand is clenched as if
clinging to something. This small hand might be seeking someone to
soothe its loneliness.>

name: Doll's Right Leg
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:Doll's right leg. From the moist heat, one can feel the vitality
dwelling in the doll. The balance and size of the leg clearly indicate
that it belongs to a child.>

name: Doll's Left Leg
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:Doll's left leg. The slightly warm leg feels thin and very delicate.
It must be modeled after a well-cared-for child from a good family.>

name: Doll's Head
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:Doll's head. The long, beautiful black hair and the white, well-
arranged features are just like Saku. It seems that this doll was
indeed made in the image of Saku.>

name: Bath Set
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:Bathing supplies found indoors. A camellia-scented shampoo and a white
soap were stored unopened. They seem usable as they are well-
preserved.>

description:
A worn-out dry cell battery. There's only one, but
it might still be able to power a small device.
name: Old Battery
note: HideItemNumber

name: Strawberry Cake
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:Strawberry cake. It is beautifully decorated with whipped cream. It
seems to be for celebrating someone's birthday, but not a single bite
has been taken.>

name: Birthday Candle
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:A candle colored with red and green pigments. Perhaps the small,
unused candle was meant to celebrate someone.>

description:
A cake decorated with six candles and
strawberries. The child who was supposed to be
celebrated never got to see a birthday cake until
the end.
name: Birthday Cake
note:
HideItemNumber

note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:A remote control found in a private house. It's dirty, but it seems
like it could still be used if batteries are put in. It's probably for
operating the room's air conditioning system.>

description:
A remote control found in a private house. If you
insert batteries and turn it on near the air
conditioner, you can alleviate the scorching heat
of the room.
name: Remote Control with Batteries
note:
HideItemNumber

description:
A small ignition device found in the garden. The
fuel is scant, but there is enough left for a few
uses.
name: Lighter
note: HideItemNumber

name: Red Key of Paired Wings
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:A key found in a western-style mansion. It has a grip shaped like a
bird with one wing, and a small red gem is inlaid. Perhaps the bird
with matching wings was able to find its other half.>

name: Blue Key of Paired Wings
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:A key found in a western-style mansion. It has a grip shaped like a
bird with one wing, and a small blue gem is inlaid. Perhaps the bird
with matching wings was able to find its other half.>

name: Doll's Eye
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:Doll's eyes. They are the same color as Saku's eyes, but a clearer and
deeper shade. They appear to have been carefully stored by someone, as
there is not a speck of dust on them.>

name: Doll's Heart
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:The heart of a doll. A heart that beats warmly, brimming with
vitality. It is clear that this is the life of Sakuo, and it is the
last part that must never be missing. Let's breathe new life into
Sakuo quickly.>

name: Small Cross
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:A small cross found in a western-style mansion. Made of a light
material, perhaps for a child. Did the child who owned this have
blessings that matched their faith?>

description:
A sickle made for harvesting rice. The still sharp
blade is useful for obtaining a bountiful harvest.
name: Rice Harvesting Sickle
note: HideItemNumber

description:
The harvest of rice grown by infusing the power of
divine energy into withered rice plants. With
proper processing, it would likely become brown
rice suitable for consumption.
name: Rich Rice Ears
note: HideItemNumber

description:
Leaves of mugwort that were growing wild outside a
private house. They are fresh and green, but
inedible as they are.
name: Mugwort Leaf
note: HideItemNumber

description:
Shiitake mushrooms that were growing from a
decayed tree. They have grown splendidly, but they
seem inedible without cooking.
name: Shiitake Mushroom
note: HideItemNumber

description:
A brown rice porridge filled with mugwort and
shiitake mushrooms. The steamy bowl emits an
appetizing aroma of new rice.
name: Freshly Made Rice Porridge
note: HideItemNumber

description:
A rice ball wrapped in beautiful bamboo leaves.
Luxuriously made with white rice, it feels imbued
with certain faith and prayer.
name: Rice ball wrapped in bamboo leaves
note: HideItemNumber

name: Prayer Tachi (or Prayer Long Sword)
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:A sword found in the mansion. It appears to be very old, but it is
imbued with a deep power of prayer. With this blade, it is likely
possible to exorcise even a powerful curse.>

name: Vermilion Comb
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:The comb found in Saku's room. The red comb with moon decorations is a
relic of Saku, who was sacrificed, and it harbors the last remaining
thoughts of Saku.>

description:
A heavy brass key with a solid build. It's
terribly cold but seems sturdy enough to open a
strong door.
name: Brass Key
note: HideItemNumber

name: Stainless Key
note:
HideItemNumber

<ExtendDesc:A stainless key that shines silver. It's still new, but there's a
slight residue of a curse left on it. The owner of this must have been
defeated by the curse.>

description:
A well-made key. It has black and white decorative
cords attached, which somehow remind one of a
whaling curtain.
name: Key with a Decorative Cord
note: HideItemNumber

description:
A large key made of iron. It is heavy, but despite
its old appearance, it is not rusty at all. What
was this key protecting?
name: Iron Key
note: HideItemNumber

description:
A key made of silver. It is decorated with
extremely fine details, and a crescent moon
pattern is engraved on it.
name: Silverwork Key
note: HideItemNumber
